Suppose \(f(x,y)=xy^{2}+7\).  Compute the following values:
\par 

\par\bgroup\advance\leftskip by 2em 

\par\begin{tabular}{rcl}
\(f(4,5)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{12.5ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\(f(5,4)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{12.5ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\(f(0,0)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{12.5ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\(f(-1,5)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{12.5ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\(f(t,2t)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{12.5ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\(f(uv,u-v)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{12.5ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\end{tabular}

